<subSubSection id="C369B08A227BFFAFA9831463FC8AAF77" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227BFFAEA9831463FEE9AE02" blockId="2.[166,1224,1020,1070]" box="[166,371,1048,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">(collector unknown).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227BFFAEA9FE1434FC32AF26" blockId="2.[166,1225,1103,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: from Fennoscandia south to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEAA791434FC35AE46" box="[860,943,1103,1130]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">France</collectingCountry>
; from 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEAADF1434FBD5AE46" box="[1018,1103,1103,1130]" name="Ireland" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Ireland</collectingCountry>
eastwards through northern and central Europe (including northern 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEAA4E1414FC3EAEA6" box="[875,932,1135,1162]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Italy</collectingCountry>
), frequent in the central Alps; 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEA9CE14F4FECEAE86" box="[235,340,1167,1194]" name="Hungary" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Hungary</collectingCountry>
to European Territory of 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEABAE14F4FD40AE86" box="[651,730,1167,1194]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Russia</collectingCountry>
; Siberia and Far East of 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEAAD914F4FBD2AE86" box="[1020,1096,1167,1194]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227BFFAEAD7D14F4FF66AEE6" country="Russia" name="Magadan" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Magadan Region</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227BFFAEA82A14D4FD99AEE6" box="[271,515,1199,1226]" country="Russia" name="Khabarovsk" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Khabarovsk Region</collectingRegion>
); scattered records from Nothern America from Alaska through much of 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEA85214B4FE4BAEC6" box="[375,465,1231,1258]" name="Canada" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Canada</collectingCountry>
and south through the Rocky Mountains to Colorado (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAD4514B4FECDAF26" author="Mutin, V. A. &amp; Barkalov, A. V." pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="342 - 500" refId="ref4594" refString="Mutin, V. A. &amp; Barkalov, A. V. 1999. Fam. Syrphidae - hoverflies. In: Lehr, P. A., ed. Key to the insects of Russian Far East. Vol. 6 (Diptera and Siphonaptera), pt. 1. Dalnauka Publishing House, Vladivostok, 342 - 500 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="1999">Mutin &amp; Barkalov, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEA8471494FE7EAF26" author="Toth, S." box="[354,484,1263,1290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="5 - 408" refId="ref5241" refString="Toth, S. 2011. Magyarorszag zengolegy faunaja (Diptera: Syrphidae) [Hoverfly fauna of Hungary (Diptera: Syrphidae)]. e-ActaNaturaliaPannonica, Supplementum 1, 5 - 408. http: // epa. oszk. hu / 01900 / 01957 / 00012 / pdf / EPA 01957 _ e-acta _ nat _ pannon _ suppl _ 1 _ 2011. pdf" type="journal article" year="2011">Tóth, 2011</bibRefCitation>
; Speight, 2017); 
<collectingCountry id="F364A391227BFFAEAB861494FC99AF26" box="[675,771,1263,1290]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(first record).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCCE301227BFFAFA9FE1574FB54AED7" blockId="2.[166,1225,1103,1834]" lastBlockId="3.[171,1230,1248,1371]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Diagnosis. This species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABB7156BFC97AF05" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[658,781,1295,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABB7156BFC97AF05" box="[658,781,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. peltatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAA481574FBD6AF06" author="Young, A. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[877,1100,1295,1322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref5643" refString="Young, A. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. 2016. Revision of Platycheirus Lepeletier and Serville (Diptera: Syrphidae) in the Nearctic north of Mexico. Zootaxa, 4082 (1), 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="2016">Young et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
); it is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA801154BFDD8AF66" authority="Curran, 1927" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[292,578,1327,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA801154BFE00AF65" box="[292,410,1327,1353]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
Curran, 1927
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAB701554FCBAAF66" author="Vockeroth, J. R." box="[597,800,1327,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="659 - 766" refId="ref5405" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. 1990. Revision of the Nearctic species of Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 122 (7 - 8), 659 - 766." type="journal article" year="1990">Vockeroth, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEAA0B1554FB97AF66" author="Young, A. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[814,1037,1327,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref5643" refString="Young, A. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. 2016. Revision of Platycheirus Lepeletier and Serville (Diptera: Syrphidae) in the Nearctic north of Mexico. Zootaxa, 4082 (1), 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="2016">Young et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
) in having first tarsomere of fore leg with weak dorsal keel on apical half, but without distinct keel on basal half. Male can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAB7C150BFD56AFA5" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[601,716,1391,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAB7C150BFD56AFA5" box="[601,716,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the mid tibia with apex strongly swollen (fig. 10) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA81715EBFE3FAF85" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[306,421,1423,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA81715EBFE3FAF85" box="[306,421,1423,1449]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apex of the mid tibia weakly swollen); the “apical half of ventral surface of the mid tibia with suberect, tangled, dark pile, which is approximately equal in length to tibial diameter” (fig. 10) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAB7015ABFD5DAFC5" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[597,711,1487,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAB7015ABFD5DAFC5" box="[597,711,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the “apical half of ventral surface of the mid tibia with very short, scarcely discernible pile”); the anepimeron with pile only on upper half, and pile forming a compact tuft (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABA1166BFD6DAC05" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[644,759,1551,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABA1166BFD6DAC05" box="[644,759,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the anepimeron with at least some pile on lower half, and pile on upper half not forming a compact tuft); the wing membrane entirely trichose (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA8B9162BFD8BAC45" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1927" box="[412,529,1615,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA8B9162BFD8BAC45" box="[412,529,1615,1641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. amplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, bare area of the cell bm at most one-third as long as the cell and well separated from anterior margin (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227BFFAEABE41614FC06ACA6" author="Young, A. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[705,924,1647,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref5643" refString="Young, A. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. 2016. Revision of Platycheirus Lepeletier and Serville (Diptera: Syrphidae) in the Nearctic north of Mexico. Zootaxa, 4082 (1), 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="2016">Young et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
). From similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEAD6A160BFEC1AC86" authority="(Meigen, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEAD6A160BFB52ACA5" box="[1103,1224,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. peltatus</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
(figs 11–14) it differs by the strongly swollen apex of the mid tibia with a tuft of long hairs at the base of dilation, the hairs pointing towards the base of the tibia (fig. 10) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEA81416ABFE33ACC5" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[305,425,1743,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEA81416ABFE33ACC5" box="[305,425,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. peltatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the mid tibia only slightly swollen with a tuft of short erect hairs, as on fig. 14), the wing with the basal cell bm without distinct bare area, sometimes with “very small bare areas at bases of cells c and bm” (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227BFFAEABE7176BFCA0AD05" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[706,826,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltatus">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227BFFAEABE7176BFCA0AD05" box="[706,826,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">P. peltatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the cell bm with medial bare area in the basal half) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFA85F149BFDDBAED7" author="Vockeroth, J. R." box="[378,577,1248,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="659 - 766" refId="ref5405" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. 1990. Revision of the Nearctic species of Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 122 (7 - 8), 659 - 766." type="journal article" year="1990">Vockeroth, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; Bartsh et al., 2009; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFAA03149BFC79AED7" author="Van Veen, M. P." box="[806,995,1248,1275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 248" refId="ref5309" refString="Van Veen, M. P. 2010. Hoverflies of Northwest Europe. Identification keys to the Syrphidae. Second edition. KNNV Publishing, Utrecht, 1 - 248." type="book chapter" year="2010">
<collectingRegion id="49B72DE3227AFFAFAA03149BFCC2AED7" box="[806,856,1248,1275]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="3" pageNumber="244">Van</collectingRegion>
Veen, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
; 
