<paragraph id="8BCCE301227AFFAFA9C5157BFC8AAF77" blockId="3.[171,1230,1248,1371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244">
Note. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C739882227AFFAFA840157AFE7BAF36" authorityName="Vockeroth" authorityYear="1990" box="[357,481,1280,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Platycheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nielseni">
<emphasis id="B9073F13227AFFAFA840157AFE7BAF36" box="[357,481,1280,1306]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="244">P. nielseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male, the scutum is described as “with hairs mostly black” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFA996155BFE1AAF17" author="Vockeroth, J. R." box="[179,384,1312,1339]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="659 - 766" refId="ref5405" refString="Vockeroth, J. R. 1990. Revision of the Nearctic species of Platycheirus (Diptera, Syrphidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 122 (7 - 8), 659 - 766." type="journal article" year="1990">Vockeroth, 1990</bibRefCitation>
) or “with mixed black and yellow pile” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE29EF0227AFFAFAAA4155BFBF1AF17" author="Young, A. D. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H." box="[897,1131,1312,1339]" pageId="3" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref5643" refString="Young, A. D., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Skevington, J. H. 2016. Revision of Platycheirus Lepeletier and Serville (Diptera: Syrphidae) in the Nearctic north of Mexico. Zootaxa, 4082 (1), 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="2016">Young et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In the Ukrainian specimen the scutal hairs are mostly pale.
</paragraph>
